														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4496171">
									

<p>This is remarkably compelling for a tale where, essentially, nothing much of anything happens. I'm excited to read what it's setting the scene for: the characters feel well-rounded and real, and the world feels incredibly real as well &#8212; probably, now I come to think of it, because nothing even vaguely anomalous happens throughout. It's <em>our</em> world, but it plays that to its strength and ends up with a delightfully nostalgic vignette where nobody dies, no laws of physics are violated, and the Foundation doesn't get so much as a name-check.</p>
<p>Which, for a tale on this site, is an abnormality. But it's a testament to your skills that I didn't notice until writing this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
